Pain relief medicine (socket no. 1, uncoloured pouch. Used for fractures, extensive wounds and burns. One tablet per administration);
Remedy for AHW poisoning (nest No 2, yellow-green coloured container. It is taken by 1 capsule 20-30 min before entering the zone of smoke (gassiness), at high risk of inhalation of CO - carbon monoxide, in the burning forest, during the work on extinguishing fires and rescuing the victims);
Remedy for ODS poisoning (socket no. 3, syringe-tube with red cap. For intramuscular use. To be administered on Civil Defence signal);
Radioprotective agent No. 1 (Box No. 4, crimson-coloured container. The contents of the pouch should be taken 15-20 min before the intended exposure);
Radioprotective agent No. 2 (nest No. 5, pencil case of white colour. It is taken by adults and children on 1 tablet before the supposed exposure or within 30 minutes after the exposure. Then 1 tablet daily after fallout. For children under 2 years of age, 1/3 tablet);
Antibacterial agent No. 1 (socket no. 6, uncoloured pellet. To be taken in case of threatened or bacterial infection, as well as in case of wounds and burns, the contents of the pencil case, washed down with water. Banned for children under 8 years of age; from 8 to 12 years of age, 1 capsule per administration);
Antibacterial agent No. 2 (socket No. 7, uncoloured pencil case. It is administered after irradiation in case of gastrointestinal disturbances, 1 tablet 2 times a day. Children are prohibited);
Antidiarrhoeal agent (nipple no. 9, pencil case blue. Take 1 tablet immediately after exposure. For children aged 6 years and over, 1/2 tablet);
POP reserve antidote (antioxidant, slot no. 8, pouch red. The contents of the pencil case are to be taken at the Civil Defence alarm. Children 5-12 years of age take 1 tablet).

Octinisept. Indications - treatment of skin and mucous membranes before diagnostic and surgical procedures in pediatric, surgical and obstetrics-gynecological practice, in traumatology, proctology, dermatovenerology, otorhinolaryngology, dentistry;
treatment of wound and burn surfaces; prophylaxis of foot mycosis and interfinger mycosis.
        In private cases it is recommended for hypertension and semi-fainting.
